The program behaves per the examples below.

$ ./filter -g infile.bmp outfile.bmp
$ ./filter -s infile.bmp outfile.bmp
$ ./filter -r infile.bmp outfile.bmp
$ ./filter -b infile.bmp outfile.bmp
$ ./filter -e infile.bmp outfile.bmp

G: greyscale (turns image black, white, and grey)
S: sepia (turns image reddish/brownish)
R: reverse (mirror/horizontally flip)
B: blur
E: edge detection

